caption: Great food and great service
Where the local 20-somethings are at!! Great deals. Won’t break the bank. Killer al pastor tacos.

I have been to Mission many times since moving to DC in 2017. It’s an essential DC establishment... along with mission Navy Yard, Hawthorne, and The Admiral. What I have come  to love about Mission DuPont during COVID is it’s beautiful and large streetery. I feel super safe eating on the patio. The staff follow all protocols, therefore, allowing its guest to relax and have some sort of “normal” happy hour, brunch, dining experience. I had my birthday brunch last weekend, sunny and 30 degrees! We had a great table in the sun with a wonderful heater. Jeff was an awesome server. I love the margaritas, you can’t go wrong with those! We started with waffle fries to share and then I ordered then chilaquiles for my brunch item. Others order the tacos which was a nice complement after waffle fries, chips and guac. I’m so glad to see this bar doing well since COVID. I appreciate the “all hands on deck” approach and I loook forward to going back for more outings in the coming weeks.

Food was ok.. menu very limited. The bottomless wasn't worth it because the service was not good, you waited quite a bit of time before the staff returned to ask you if you wanted another, and then more time to deliver it.
Jin was amazing. Great food and drinks. Will be telling friend and family. Thank you!
Great food, drinks flowing at a reasonable price, and super nice wait staff
Their waffle fries were crispy and super good.
This place used to be so much better. Sad it went downhill. The food used to be so good, now it's just glorified bar food. The mimosas are weak, mostly OJ.
Ordered from here for the first time and the food was amazing. Highly recommend you try the shrimp taco.
Food and services was topnotch..Great food and great drinks  BRUNCH IS A MUST
Filling burritos and unique tacos. With the pandemic they've moved to ambient outdoor seating.  Just slightly on the pricier end

Bar: awesome spot for drinks located in the middle of DuPont with a vibrant atmosphere.  Food: not so great.  Ordered the chicken quesadilla, beef empanadas and pork nachos to share with another person.  As soon as I left my stomach was turned inside out and will not be going back for food.  Update: spoke to the manager and came back to dine, and NOTHING went wrong.  Had basically the same meal with no problem.  Good to know that what had happened was an anomaly!
Excellent Service!! Food was delicious!!

The food looked good and was ok. Not the best the service was slow but there was social distancing. I ordered the chips & salsa (not complementary) and before I could sample my 1st chip they delivered my entrée (fajitas).

HIGHLY recommend for a nice drinks and Mexican-American food. My party and I ordered two margarita pitchers, empanadas, taco salad, chicken quesadillas, and chips and salsa and it was AMAZING. Most importantly they split the margarita pitchers 4 ways, without us asking!! Our waitress Emily was amazing! Shoutout to you sis, real MVP!
Had a lovely evening yesterday. Very good service and delicious food. Had Margarita, Nachos, jalapeño cheddar balls & fajita.. would like to go back whenever we get a chance.😊
Great happy hour
Great food
Great Food!
It’s my second house every Saturday!!
If you're looking for a classic Mexican restaurant with good quality food this is not a place ...

Absolutely no! Not your fav Mexican place !! Atmosphere is great,  service is OK, but the food is absolutely awful. Chicken Fajita is the basic food for a Mexican restaurant and here it was all raw and tasteless!! Taco also the same, empanada too. We spent so much money on our table but didn’t eat 1/3 of it! We had to wait 45 mins to pay out!!! Waitress was so busy that she even didn’t pay attention to us. I’m so sorry but won’t ever be back.
Food was on point! Great flavors

Nice spot next to the Farmers Market. We sat outside and did not feel crowded although there are probably only 6 tables outside. Service was very good. I had the burrito with chicken, and it was fresh and fantastic. My wife had the taco salad which was equally delicious according to her. Would have liked a table umbrella or some shade, but I would definitely go here again.
Totally average at best
A lot of food for your money
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
DC streetery is in full force!  High end Mexican food with great happy hour prices and delicious. Recommend the "piggy" tacos!!!
Graet and delicious.  Thank you !

Friendly staff, really good huevos rancheros. Margaritas are so-so. TVs are on, but no sound...so don’t expect to be able to hear a Caps/Nats game. If there is a bachelorette party, expect it to be super loud.
Nice atmosphere and very personal service. The menu was fresh and delightful. Will definitely recommend this place to anyone. Fair rates and big portions. Keep up the great work.
Get the unlimited brunch ! It’s so worth it ! And don’t forget to get your free tequila shot with that! The pork tacos are THE BEST !

We had a team happy hour at Mission recently, and it could not have been easier to arrange. Their team responded within minutes to our request, and they were able to reserve a group of tables for 15+ people at no extra charge. They also made a sign to signal to our team where to go, which was a thoughtful touch. We will definitely be heading back there again for more happy hours in the future!

Fun Mexican restaurant! Love coming here when the weather is warm because of the awesome outdoor seating. Wish they kept duck nachos on the menu but their regular nachos are pretty good. Great option for a group because of the fun atmosphere and pitchers of margaritas. The new location at navy yard is even better!

The service from Katy Perry (Erin) Is spot on perfect ... attentive , friendly, and smiley.  Extremely guest focused creating guest loyalty.    The manager David Is wonderful terrific energy , attitude, and attention to details . I enjoyed the entire experience thanks Erin and David !!!

Great spot for drinks and food. Restaurant that turns into a bar kinda dance bar. It does have a decent dj..so you can probably do requests and they have a reduced menu late night when most other places close by are not serving food! I like the chorizo sliders😀. It's a great spot for dates and chilling.
Over from Ireland, first time in Washington. Absolutely loved this place. Staff so nice and food was excellent.
Great food and good happy hour pricing on drinks!
Wow, very good and strong Cadillac Magharitas.
Great Dupont Margarita and awesome steak quesadillas. Service is great!

Me and my boyfriend came here for a date and LOVED it! Very cozy aesthetic vibes. Their homemade chips were SO good and their guacamole was outstanding. We both got the taco trio and loved it. Their staff was friendly and helpful. We will definitely be coming back here.

I highly recommend hosting events at Mission Dupont! Kati and her team were so easy to work with. She was responsive and accommodating of all of our group's changes of plans and made coordinating the event really stress-free. The event itself was really successful too. We hosted a networking happy hour and everyone walked away saying how fun the environment was, how conducive the rooms/set up were to networking, and how great the food and drinks were. Prices felt fair for how much we got, and not having a room rental fee was a huge bonus. We'll definitely be going back to Mission to host future events!

I have always loved this restaurant and I hosted a work event at this location. The event went really well from the planning to the execution. Staff was responsive, friendly, and helpful throughout the planning and the day of. Would  100% recommend the upstairs loft. It was private with its own bar and the noise from downstairs did not travel up. The pricing is also phenomenal.  Needless to say great food and drinks.
Had a great brunch here the other day. They were very accommodating and didn’t make the non drinkers do the bottomless option. And the drinkers had a great time! Great guacamole too!

Had an event at Mission for a work event. It was a great time!! Leading up to the event, the staff was extremely accommodating and very friendly. During the event, food and drinks came out quickly and the customer service was great! Highly recommend this place for work happy hours!
BAD COLD TACOS
Just had dinner (valentines day) my wife and I. .....The peanut head girl(Avi) was less than attentive.  I mean really sucked.
Good food, good service, good price too

Hosted a fabulous dinner for 24 people last night at Mission Dupont! Everyone had a great time-the food and the service were excellent! Kati was amazing to work with to get the event set up. Highly recommend for a fun, relaxed event in a great location!!!!
This place is awesome. I love it. Great food, good price, good atmosphere.

I had my birthday party, back in June, at Mission and it was one of the best parties I have ever had! Kati was so communicative and worked with me to make sure that I had a space reserved for my party and some drink/food specials. My friends and I had the best time, and  I would absolutely recommend Mission for your next party! They will make sure you have an amazing time!
Best happy hour, get the cauliflower!
Fun environment. Awesome food. Real good brunch option.

Horrible NYE. So many better options.  Bad service.  $100 entry with advertised open bar.  No shots and limited drinks. The event advertised food, but we couldn’t find any.  Boring crowd and poor atmosphere. Save your time and money.
It was fine. Great space for a small holiday party.
Good service (Sharanya), good Mexican food.
Service great.  Food mediocre
Best guacamole ever.
(Translated by Google) Free margaritas  (Original) Grat margaritas
Loves the quesadilla and the nachos for happy hour. Reasonable prices, large portions, good margaritas, and everything tasted quite fresh.
Great place - free group hosting for happy hours

This is a great place for brunch. For $38 you get bottomless mimosas, margs, bloody Mary’s and 1 shot of tequila along side an entree. I had the tacos and they were pretty good. The service was quick but this place gets pretty crowded. I would come back to celebrate an event but definitely make a reservation.
I love the margaritas and the food is pretty good too. They have several bar seats, but seating area usually requires prior reservation.
The telephone booth upstairs is GREAT for photos

Mission was ok. Had the enchiladas and they were somewhat warm. Beans had hardly any flavor to them. Basmati rice with mexican food? Hardly Mexican. Coffee tasted like it was filtered through an old sock. Wait staff was friendly and very good. Had the Dupont Margarita, a little light on the alcohol but tasty.
Great margaritas and fun atmosphere. Had a really great happy hour with a group!

What a terrible family style brunch. The food was mediocre. They sat our party next to the bar, near the entrance and I’m using the word “sat” loosely bc there were a couple of stools placed along the wall, not enough for our group, and then 2 tables pushed together near the window so we weren’t actually sitting at the table. When the food came out, the waiters just put the food on the table and didn’t bring us plates or silverware. We had to keep asking the hostess for these items. We had to keep asking the hostess when the rest of the food was coming out. We had to keep asking the bartender for our drinks. What terrible service and food. Not worth the $45 I spent that day. Shoutout to the hostess tho for doing other people’s job. But if I could give this place negative 5 stars, I would! Never again.
--Good location. --Good food. --Good service. --The space is a bit tight inside. The upstairs private room is nice.
Disappointed in the quality of service.

Service and the atmosphere were pleasant but oh the food..! How can Mexican food go so wrong? Shrimp taco tasted like soap and green crispy chicken was way too salty. I don't think this place deserves four stars at all (current average). Very disappointing.
Good service, happy hours are great!
Good food and friendly atmosphere
Great food. Good venue. Wonderful staff. The noise level was a bit too high for my taste. Otherwise, I would have given them 5 stars.

I had set up a post-proposal celebration event at Mission Dupont and had a blast! We had around 30 people come and go, but everyone had a great time! I coordinated the event with Kati and she was super helpful with answering all my questions and getting things sorted. We even came early and were able to use the space. I definitely recommend any of Mission's spaces for events! It was incredibly easy to organize, and it's also in a great location - perfect for any kind of celebration or get together!

I had a breakfast burrito and steak quesadilla on Saturday at opening. Bartender was Erin.  I was not greeted, or offered a menu. I had to pick a menu myself from the host's area/entrance. This review is not for the food, but more so my experience with the service with my particular bartender, Erin, and the response by the general manager, Devon.  It took about forty minutes for my meal and about thirty of that was waiting for food, or waiting for Erin to take my order. I was checked on once (how is your food) when I asked Erin for extra sauce for my quesadillas. In the entire forty minutes, neither bartenders, or any employee checked up on my water. If I remember correctly, I had to ask the male bartender and Erin, for water twice per person (total 4x).  I told the GM, Devon exactly what I posted above and said it was the worst bar experience I had in Arlington or DC. Devon said she was "sorry" and claimed that it was unusual for the two bartenders who were currently working at the time.  Devon said sorry about four times and then gave me the impression of what more do you want from me and stop wasting my time.  Devon told me to give them another chance another day. Devon did not offer to comp anything (not that I asked) on a $30 brunch. Devon never said she would talk to the bartenders or get them better trained.  To be honest, I'm not surprised by the response considering Devon and the other employees were chatting it up most of the time at the end of the bar (near the kitchen entrance) I was there.  If the owner or upper management sees this review I am curious what the response will be. I'm sure you can look at the video of the bar area yourself and confirm this. I talked to a friend who has been a bartender for a few years and she said it is probably just a bad business based on the service and GM response. Take that however you want.  Might as well just get burritos at Chipotle if you're in Dupont. What a waste of time.
Beautiful place!!!!!! AMAZING FOOD AND DRINKS!!!

I went to Mission for a small after wedding happy hour event. Chandler, our event manager and the staff were absolutely phenomenal. The team made something small and intimate absolutely amazing!! The food and drinks were fantastic and the atmosphere was exactly what we wanted for our guest! Everyone that attended loved it and were making plans to go back on their own. Perfect location, food, and staff! We loved it!!! Thank you so much Mission for making our day even more amazing!

A few weeks ago, I stopped by for a drink and some apps by myself. It was full, so I thought this place must be good. I was not disappointed. I definitely enjoyed my time, so 2 weeks later I decided to host my mother's surprise bday dinner there. Of course she thought it would only be my brother and I. Turn out was 16 ppl in all and the manager, David was so accommodating. He was personable, professional, and made my mother's night even better, when he brought out her bday cake! When I made the reservations I requested the lovely gentlemen I had my first time there, Diego. He was prompt, funny, and just had a great attitude! Thank you Mission for a wonderful experience. Can't wait to go back.
Good drinks and giant plates of nachos.  Prices are surprisingly reasonable for DC!  Can get pretty noisy, but...that's how this city is.
I reserved the 'Loft' for a birthday party with a 2 hour open bar...they took great care of us! So fun and had a great time!
Service was bit slow,  but our server  Carlos was very nice and polite.  Food was good,  had Carne Asada.  Mine was cooked well and was very good.
Checks all the boxes. Reasonably priced, generous portions, good service. Patio is lovey.

Went for brunch with some friends and the food was tasty (how can you go wrong with bottomless guac?), service was good, though they were pretty busy.  The alcohol included in the bottomless brunch is PLENTIFUL--they gave us two pitchers for a table of four, plus tequila shots.  You definitely have to pace yourself, but was still a lot of fun!
Great service!!! Best Margaritas in town!!!

The atmosphere at the bar and the drinks are great. They usually have 90s- 2000’s hip hop playing and are obviously appealing to a younger crowd. I have to admit though that the girlfriend and I only go here during happy hour. It is surprisingly expensive outside of that time frame. Food is clearly made with some degree of expertise and care.
Great ambience. Fun pkace
Great nachos!
Hosted a birthday party h ere in one of the event rooms and the staff was super helpful, brought the food out in time and worked with us to arrange across separate tabs. Thank you Mission!
Solid bottomless brunch. Unlimited guac is amazing, but breakfast burrito was just okay. Drinks are plentiful but not incredible.

Awesome experience setting up a happy hour here for my group on short notice. Process of reserving some space for my group on a Friday night was smooth and easy. Great drinks, friendly staff, and located in a great spot in Dupont right by metro for easy access. Will be returning!
Server was great and very attentive, food was excellent and reasonably priced

I used Mission DuPont for a grad school happy hour and they were so easy to work with and get everything set up. They reserved an area at the front bar for us and had a table set up with water and chips and salsa. They were very understanding and give you a location in the resturant based on how big the event is. There was no reservation fee and they were very good at staying in contact the week of the event. On top of just being an amazing place to have an event the food is amazing, would recommend the nachos and queso dip. I will be using this restaurant again for future events.
The chicken was dry.

We reserved space at Mission DuPont during happy hour to celebrate my coworker's upcoming wedding. Mission staff was super accommodating, blocked off a comfortable amount of space for us, and even decorated our reservation sign for us! I highly recommend reserving space at Mission for events.

The place to brunch when you're sure the rest of your day is empty...the drinks are strong, your cup is never empty, and the service is the best. Perfect for big groups. Also, skip the "French toast..."
This place is wonderful! Definitely do the bottomless brunch. Best taco was the pork one. Guacamole was to die for, and that is coming from a San Antonio girl!!!! Astrid was a great server.

WORST bar I've ever been in my life & worse organization! I waited more than 20 minutes for a table outside when there were empty tables! A couple arrived after me and the woman became very rough and aggressive with the staff just because they wanted a table outside just like us and they gave them our place, it was very rude! I’m really disappointed with this place. Don’t waste your time and money.
Food is great. Margaritas and Sangria are a little sweet, but still delicious.

I visited here several times and always i had good experience here and the services they provide was superb. The atmosphere was cozy and the location was awesome. The way they treat their customers was also appreciable. If i talk about the price was also decent for their food ans quick services . Finally recommended place for food lovers .
Very good tacos and great margaritas!
Went there for the first time today. The draft beers are cool, DuPont margarita is ayt. But that shrimp burrito!!!!!!! I almost went to the kitchen to give the chef a damn hug. That burrito smacked.
Despite tons of people in the restaurant we were turned away as "closing early" and told we should just Uber somewhere else. Skip this restaurant
Mission Dupont is a great place to host happy hours and networking events. Their friendly staff make it is easy to coordinate and organize events.
I went there for brunch and It was great. I recommend to take the brunch menu.  It can get very crowded  so I recommend to make a reservation.
Excellent taco's & guacamole

Food was actually okay (nothing remarkable, simply okay) but cutlery looked dirty, even if it came out of dishwasher it looked ugly, time to buy new ones (or wash properly)...what annoyed me at the very beginning is that although we wanted to sit outside we were asked to go inside to talk to the host if we can be seated outside....perhaps the “host” could have mandated the waiters outside to lead us to one of the empty tables or could also have come out to great us.
Food takes forever but it's good!

I only stayed for one drink, but wanted to drop a note on how friendly and helpful the staff were! It’s nice to be greeted with a smile. Everyone was so accommodating to our party and super flexible. I’m not going to lie, in DC it’s hard to get good customer service, but Mission at DuPont is the exception.
Phil is the best the waiter I ever had, he’s knowledgeable on the menu, fun loving personality and is very professional. I recommend you get him as service and take his recommendations
Phil is the best waiter I ever had, he kind and he’s knowledgeable on everything this restaurant have to offer. I definitely recommend his services and the meals
The food was good, but it was so loud that you couldn't hear the people sitting right beside you. Some soundproofing is in order.

Wish I could give zero stars. Where to start... too noisy for any conversation. My husband and I ordered burritos - they were lukewarm and the rice was not fully cooked. The only non-meat “protein” that could be added to the burrito was portobello mushroom. Portobello mushrooms have virtually no protein to them. There are other non-meat protein sources that would work in burritos.  So we won’t be back and most definitely would not recommend this restaurant.
Decent food with a really nice and trendy atmosphere.

I just hosted a surprise birthday party at Mission and it couldn't have been a better experience!  I worked with Kati and she was extremely responsive and had everything setup when I arrived.  We had the back bar area, which allowed us to be separated from the crowd, but have easy access to the bar. I would absolutely recommend Mission to anyone looking to host an event.
Great place for our event
The food is good, 2-3 steps up from bar food. It is always impossible to sit outside. The margaritas are good though

Good food, but not the best drinks/bar atmosphere. I've been twice-- once just for drinks and once for dinner. The drinks were okay, but the atmosphere wasn't very lively. We ended up leaving and going elsewhere. The food, though, was great! I haven't been able to find good, sit-down vegetarian Mexican food in the area and this was pretty tasty. I loved the chile rellanos. I thought it was a little pricey, but I think it's on par for the area. I'd recommend the food, but maybe go to a bar somewhere else.
The nachos and tacos were delicious, and atmosphere has a great vibe. The only thing keeping from giving 5 stars is that the wait staff needs to be more attentive to the customers.
Good deals for happy hour!
Food was pretty good, but everything tasted like and had celery in it.
No place for a group

Beware any place that has margaritas on tap. I'm sure there's alcohol in there somewhere but at $8 a glass it feels a lot like high class juice with salt on the rim. At least I can recommend the sangria. But the atmosphere is cool and the tacos keep you coming back.

Hosted a happy hour on a Thursday night in the back bar space at Mission Dupont. The process to reserve the space was easy and the events planner (Kati) was very responsive, friendly, and put together exactly what we needed. It's tough to find bars in DC that will reserve space without a fee or a minimum so the fact that Mission does is especially clutch for small to medium group outings.  Bartenders were awesome and it was a fun atmosphere for a post-work event. Would definitely recommend hosting your work or group happy hour here.

I went in here for my 21st birthday with high hopes, but I was completely disappointed once the food arrived at the table. It was bland, tasteless, unseasoned. No wonder this establishment is so popular amongst caucasians. The service was amazing, all servers that approached our table were attentive, smiling, and quick to complete our requests. Too bad the food does match the level of service they offer. Lastly, I’d also like to point out the music was too loud and it didn’t fit the theme of the restaurant. All in all, this place is just a mockery of Mexican culture, someone had to say it.
Beautiful on the inside.
Terrific
Waste of money.
happy hour margarita spot 🤩🤩🤩
Huge restaurant with a small menu. That's really the best thing I can say about it

I visited with a group of about a dozen other people.  The other's appeared to enjoy their food, but unfortunately the kitchen served me something other than I ordered.  The server confirmed the mistake was theirs (I ordered and she copied the right item down, but the wrong item was served.)  When I pointed it out, she notified the kitchen who hastily prepared my order and did not cook the fish all the way.  We all know that large groups take a while to serve, which normally isn't an issue, but when you make a mistake like this what ends up happening is the meal goes back for a third try as my friends are finishing their meal.  The server did *not* offer to comp my meal--the meal I had not even eaten yet, by the way--and offered me a free beer to "thank me for my patience."  Things then went south as I became very very hangry.  I honestly gave up on them at that point, left my group and went somewhere else for a meal.  The rest of them seemed to enjoy the meal, but I was too hungry to wait for another meal.

okay food with cool atmosphere Colma nothing to write home about with regards The Culinary experience. I spend there some time with friends it was fun very loud looks like the service season be exhausted only know a good place to hang out
Bottomless brunch my a**.  Spent $50 for barely even a full meal and not even a buzz, despite chugging several mimosas. They served hardly any food for our group and watered down the drinks.
Crowded on Friday evening... but if you can be out by 7 they will work with you on inside seating.

Ventured here for a co-workers last hurray.  I wasn't really impressed.  They have an ubandance of tequila, but don't carry 1800 - that's odd to me. Exepensive shots.  All female bartendars.  Had to ask a few times for chips and dip.  Nothing to run home and tell your friends about.  Oh, and it's extremely loud in there.  You have to repeat yourself a couple of times before the bartendar or server can understand what you're saying.

TERRIBLE SERVICE - DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY! If I could give this place 0 stars, I would. We were visiting from out of state, and were looking for a place to sit outside and eat. We walked in and sat at the bar (because you cannot order anywhere other than the bar, and they will NOT bring you your food if you're not at the bar) to order. There were 3 servers working behind the bar (a white man with blonde hair, a white woman with brown hair, and a black/mixed woman). We waited, and waited, and waited...for over 10 minutes just waiting for someone to acknowledge us and ask to take our order. That never happened. We finally had to FLAG someone down, and when we did, she acted irritated that we were wanting service. We placed our order and after 20 minutes, it arrived...HALF OF MY ORDER MISSING and was given NO EATING UTENSILS, NAPKINS, OR DRINKS. At this point, we didn't want to even bother asking for anything because we just wanted to get out of the LOUDEST bar I have ever been to (SO LOUD THE SERVERS COULD NOT HEAR THE PATRONS). We walked outside to sit down and there were NO SEATS because NON-PAYING PATRONS were using the seating area for PAYING CUSTOMERS to socialize. Even after all this, we decided it wasn't worth it to bring up another issue to the staff, since they all seemed irritated and less than helpful, so we walked back inside to find a table somewhere. After walking around back, we found several empty tables and decided to sit. However, as we started to sit (STILL HALF MY ORDER MISSING AND NO EATING UTENSILS, NAPKINS OR DRINK), another employee (black woman) told us we could not sit there because we needed reservations and if we wanted to sit there, we had to walk BACK up to the front, stand in line (behind 10-12 other people), check in with the hostess, and be seated. At this point, I had reached my boiling point and asked for a manager, only to find out, the black woman who told me I had to go back up front and wait in line with my FOOD GETTING COLD, STILL MISSING HALF MY ORDER, STILL WITH NO EATING UTENSILS, STILL WITH NO NAPKINS, AND STILL WITH NO DRINK, was the MANAGER. I told her what the issue was and rather than apologize and help us, by seating us and taking the initiative to handle whatever their "policy" was about being seated in an EMPTY ROOM within the eatery/bar, she was incredibly rude and stated, "It really is a simply concept." It was clear this place had NO IDEA WHAT CUSTOMER SERVICE is, which is a "SIMPLE CONCEPT" especially when you're in the CUSTOMER SERVICE INDUSTRY. Furthermore, it was clear they were not interested in paying customers or tips. We asked for our money back, left our food, and went to another wonderful eatery where we HEAVILY TIPPED the wonderful staff. The Mission needs a COMPLETE EMPLOYEE OVERHAUL. Unbelievable.
Great place, have never had a bad experience here. Literally right of the q street exit from DuPont metro station you can not get lost going home no matter how many margaritas you have.

Mission is by far my favorite restaurant in the Dupont area. The salmon as well as the vegan tacos are fantastic. The outdoor patio is the perfect place to eat some fabulous food and drink a cold margarita on a nice summer evening. Whether at night or midday for brunch, Mission Dupont is a must-try!
Good choices
Great place to meet friends foods great prices are good

Our DC Women's Happy Hour Meetup met at Mission and they helped make our event a great success! They set up a sign for our space and the tables and room were perfectly arranged. Food and drinks were delicious. Couldn't have asked for more!

Great place to host a happy hour! The staff are easy to work with and they have several areas that don’t require a room reservation fee or a minimum F&B purchase, which makes it an easy place to have a small to medium-sized gathering.

I love this place! I have a lot of things I cannot eat for health reasons, and they went out of their way to accommodate. Friends with intolerances or allergies of any kind, this place will help you and make sure you leave healthy and happy. Thank you Mission DuPont! I appreciate you all.

Now I liked it very much. My husband did not. Caveat... we'd been day drinking and stopped at the first Mexican restaurant we could find in the evening. Had a great waiter and I really liked the food. Price was good too.

Margaritas were on point, quesadillas were delicious, but the real treat was our server. If you're not being waited on by Phil, ask to be moved to his section. He was extremely attentive, friendly, and it'd be a sin to not mention that he's beautiful to look at. Highly recommend all around.
Fun place, good food.
Great tacos, even for this discerning California native. A little loud.

DO NOT EAT HERE! We did an 11 person brunch and out of the group 7 of us got sick. 2 were so violently ill thy they almost had to be hospitalized. The ambiance and service and service were fine but the aftermath of the meal was brutal. If you decide to eat there you are rolling the dice on getting a sickness that I would not wish upon my worst enemies.
Amazing, so good
One of my favorite places in DC for brunch with a large group - they're super accommodating and can help host any event that you might think of! and the margaritas are amazing!

Server was great, and the food was satisfying.  Perhaps the loudest restaurant we visited in D.C., it was impossible to hold a conversation really, so our time there was short.  Don't know how to accomplish this, but if it was a few decibels quieter and there were some more vegan offerings then I'd give 5 stars.
meh
Amazing event space and great margaritas!
Food: 4/5 Price: 4/5 Service: 5/5 Restaurant: 4/5.

ZIP YOUR PURSE AND HOLD WALLET CLOSE.  This rating is not related to the food but to my experience at this restaurant. The food was great. The customer service and staff were far from it. It must have been an employee because none of the tables around us left while we were there and my cards were charged at a liquor store a couple blocks away from the restaurant while we were there. They have cameras, but claimed they were "fuzzy" which was no help and pretty useless. Both Mission locations are awesome! My company hosted an event at the DuPont Location and everything was exceptional. They had an area cleared out for us and we had incredible service the entire time. I will definitely be back to have more events here!

Food looks good , satisfying for the taste buds, the drinks could be a little stronger tho

Decided to throw a party for my girlfriend's birthday here and my experience was great. No hassle and a very polite and responsive staff. I will definitely tell my friends about throwing private events here.

We had an end of the year get-together at Mission at the end of December and one thing I can say about Mission above anything else is that their correspondence is stellar. They were accommodating to our group size, expedient when it came to drinks, and the reservation loft space was spacious enough to fit our group of 30+ people.  Between that and the happy hour prices for margaritas and quesadillas, this is a very great location that I would wholeheartedly recommend for visiting if you're either in the D.C. or, more specifically, the Dupont Circle area. And our bartender, Letty, was excellent from start to finish. Would very much suggest paying Mission a visit.

Great food & maprgaritas!

I recently visited Mission for a small birthday gathering for a family member. From the outside Mission  looks pretty small but to my surprise, there is plenty of space inside. I recently organized an event at Mission Dupont. It was seamless to arrange - Kati is great to work with! I really recommend Mission for private events in the Dupont Circle area.

I went there for an alumni happy hour so I don’t know what the prices are like but they had a good variety of food. It was solid Mexican but definitely not authentic, due to its lack of flavor (namely salt).

IF YOU ARE FROM TEXAS, DO NOT EAT HERE!!  That's being said...  My girlfriend and I are on vacation in DC. We are both from Texas. Meaning, when it comes to Tex-Mex or authentic Mexican food, we have a bit of experience.  Firstly, this place was VERY crowded for what I would expect on a Thursday night. Lots of college kids, and a few business type individuals. Had to wait 30 minutes to be seated. I didn't rate this restaurant 1 star for this, as it can happen with any restaurant.  Only thing that was very aggravating, is how loud it was. We were sitting two feet away from each other, and had to resort to texting, to be able to hold a conversation. College kids being loud and obnoxious, with loud music (sounded like dubstep or something with very heavy bass) playing over the speakers.  Our waiter was MIA (missing in action) for 95% of the time. Once we did get our food, we did not have any silverware. I ended up asking a different waiter for some, since we couldn't find ours. This waiter only brought one set. I ended up going up to the hostess for second set.  For the food itself:  The salsa was.... Okay. They have green and red salsa. Both are not spicy whatsoever. Chips were passable.  I ordered the enchilada plate, and she ordered the burrito.  My girlfriend order a burrito. She only ate about a fourth of it before calling it quits. Basically, it just was not good.  My enchiladas arrived cold the beef was mediocre, the chicken tasted like it was something processed (think McNuggets from McDonald's). The cheese one was... Acceptable. The side of rice was chewy and cold. I did not try the side of beans, so I don't have an opinion.  We ended up having to get a hold of the manager in order to pay our bill. We did pay it in full, but due to the terrible service from the waiter, we did not leave a tip. The manager was very nice and accommodating. We did not take our left overs.  For the rest of our vacation, we will not chance eating Mexican food again.

We we're seated right away. Our waitress was friendly and helpful. We ordered the margaritas and they did not disappoint. The guacamole was excellent. I do wish the chips were warm. The tacos are excellent. I ordered the shrimp, choirzo, and pork belly. The choirzo and shrimp we're my favorite. I would definitely love to try others. Mission is a fun place to eat and would definitely be a place I would try again.
Friendly service with quality food. The margaritas were very good! Nice bar to watch something with friends.
A different eating experience with good  service and a big portion culture. Could be a winner for big appetites.

Food is top notch. Great service and atmosphere.

Very popular restaurant! Make reservations if it is a weekend night. Good margaritas, good chips and salsa. The corn-on-the-cob extravaganza was ridiculous (in a good way). Tacos were good. OK... I travel quite a bit and sample restaurants all over the world.  I had a meeting in Dupont Circle so I decided to try Mission for the first time.  Even though this is in a very busy area, there is plenty of street parking after 6:30 pm on Massachusetts Ave NW. The restaurant has a great ambiance with a rustic feel and not the over the top Mexican place.  The menu was simple and easy to order from.  I went with the taco platter.  I don't normally say this but the service was Freeky Fast.  The order was well presented (see photo) and the food was good.  I normally don't order desert, but everything was going so well.. why not?  The Churros are made in house.  They took a bit longer, but I appreciated getting them freshly prepared and super crispy.  The accompanying chocolate sauce was a great surprise... It had a spice/kick to it.  It was a great match for Churros.  Overall.. great place and I will be back.
Great Mexican food and strong margaritas! This restaurant is so cute and the staff are very attentive. Very reasonably priced for DC and can't wait to go back!
Waitress was friendly but food wasn't good. Salmon didn't taste good.

Food was very good. Service was good. They did mess up my order but the remake was fast. They have a patio but it was hot so I elected to sit inside. While I was offered a table I decided to eat at the bar. Cozy inside. I would go here again.

It's conveniently located near Dupont Metro. This makes it a good meeting place. Prices are reasonable. The interior is very noisy as it becomes full. Food is average. Service is good. I wouldn't intentionally go there nor would I refuse to go, if others wanted to meet there.
I hosted a surprise birthday party event here and overall it went well! My only complaint is that the back bar area only had enough chairs for 6 people, I can't imagine trying to fit 30 back there.

One of the best places I’ve been to in the area! Went with friends to celebrate a birthday. ANNA was our server and she was soooo good! We will return.

I have attended several private events at Mission. They have great spaces (a back bar/front bar area, side rooms that are semi private, etc.). Our waiter checked in frequently and they made sure we had everything we needed; she even split up the bill at the end of the night when there was 12+ of us! Also the drinks and food are so good and come out super quick. I will never stop raving about their nachos! All in all, would recommend going to Mission to anyone in all regards.

I hosted my birthday brunch here and it was amazing. I made a reservation about a month ago and they were very attentive and patient with me with my ever changing headcount. The room was a bit snug but everyone had a seat and the food was …

Mediocre mexican food. A bit over priced, taco was way over sauced. The night we went was our waiters first night. He was pretty bad at the job. He also dropped roughly 8 glasses for the table next to us and then proceeded to drop the replacements.

I spent the afternoon at Mission for my wife's birthday and I could not have asked for a better experience.  They were able to give our group a reserved area even though it was one of their busiest days.  The staff was incredible, helpful, and accommodating.  The food and drinks were on point, everyone left satisfied and full.  I would recommend Mission to anyone looking for a great Mexican restaurant in DC.

I planned a happy hour here for work and it went over very smoothly! Their event planning team was fast to respond and reserved an area for us. The bartenders were super friendly and didn't leave us waiting for drinks. And of course, the margaritas and appetizers were delicious! Don't miss the queso dip while you're there!

Mission is a really fun spot in the heart of DC. The Margaritas we great, especially the strawberry basil marg. The food was good. I had the tres amigos(?), which were 3 enchiladas (chicken, cheese and pork). Honestly, I didn’t care much for the cheese enchilada or the Mission Marg, which is the signature marg, but didn’t seem like anything special to me.  We came in at 8pm, and waited an hour at the bar for patio seating. Service felt slow, but it was packed in there so I understand.  Great atmosphere, I would go again for the drinks and ambiance.

I was having some trouble finding suitable meeting space for a large group, but luckily found Mission, and they made it really easy to utilize a small space for a large group. They had a small room (no door) off the main dining area that can fit up to (probably 15). Although you can hear the noise from the dining area--I went on a Thursday evening during happy hour which was probably poor timing--it is still quiet enough to hear everyone at the table. For even larger groups, they have a loft upstairs that is more private and definitely quieter. The staff I spoke with in advance was great and very accommodating, and the wait staff was great as well. We will definitely be utilizing Mission again! There's not many places in the DC area that are so accommodating for large groups at no cost--which is vital as an NGO volunteer in need of space!
Great Mexican food

I hosted a happy hour here for a group from work and the staff could not have been more helpful. Mission was the only restaurant in the area I found that offered a reserved spot for any number of people (my group was about 50) without a fee. I organize a monthly happy hour and we all pay our own tabs and Mission was accommodating in giving us a designated spot that was large enough for our group and allowed had no minimum bill requirements. They even posted signs in the designated area so everyone would know where our group was when they walked in! I definitely plan to host another event here. Sometimes we have a guest speaker and the upstairs space is private enough to hear someone speak while still having a fun environment! Thanks to Fritz!

I hosted my 26th birthday party at Mission. Over the course of four hours the bartender Gina gracefully and patiently served the ~30+ friends that came in and out of the loft bar. Setting up the event was effortless as the owner Fritz was always responsive and forward thinking when it came to the event. I highly recommend Mission if you are ever looking for a place to host a fun event!
Great food and service. Simple menu and they do it well. The happy hour deals were good and included food.

I refrained from reviewing because I had only ever come for fundraisers or special events. But I brought my family here for brunch when they were in town this week. We had the breakfast bowls and had an order of nachos with carnitas. I would definitely recommend.

This place has great service and is amazing at arranging any sort of event you may have in mind; happy hours, rehearsal dinner, etc. I hosted my birthday party at the bar and was so relieved to find a place that helped me with every detail I asked for. I would definitely host another event here as I do love their quesadillas and margaritas, specially the pineapple jalapeño margarita. It's a winner!
Great service! The fancy margarita wasn't as good as the house margarita. I would definitely go here again.

This is a great go to place very versatile, but they disappoint by getting rid of or changing tasty authentic things on the menu. Their brunch chilaquiles served on a skillet made with corn chips was fantastic. The new version is heavy and ordinary. Same with the elote.

Went to Mission just around 10PM on a Saturday with some friends and we were thoroughly disappointed. The food was quite mediocre. My carne asada was nearly cold when I received it. Mission is great for large parties. I have been here twice - Once with 12 people, and the second time with around 16. Both times we had amazing service: drinks came out promptly, food came out piping hot and timed well, water was refilled, and the waitress often came to check on us. They also give split checks without complaint, which is a gem for large parties. The food is reasonably priced and delicious (I got tacos, but the fajitas looked amazing). Also, try the white sangria! I'm usually not a sangria fan, but it's so delicious that our entire table chose to order it by the end of the dinner! Overall, best deal for your money in Dupont as a large party.
I’ve gone to Mission multiple time for happy hour. They have a good deal on margaritas, but there is almost never seating, and it can be quite loud.

The happy hour deals here are great and the staff is so sweet an accommodating. I am planning on attending their New Years event and had some trouble with my ticket. When I called to get some assistance I was given an email for better …

We held our company holiday party there this year and it was fantastic. The event coordinator was very flexible to our needs and budget and very responsive to requests. The food, drink, and staff at the event were all a total hit with the employees. We would definitely have our event there again.
The tacos were good and if you complain about the chips and salsa you’re a dingus. The margaritas are only so so.
Great place!
Margs are stiff and one of the only places in DC that has queso blanco. I bit pricy, but great.

Mission is the classic place to go after work in DuPont for happy hour margaritas and chips and salsa. Both in the bar area and at tables the space is really loud and the food is consistent if underwhelming. I vote coming in for their drinks on special and ease of getting a group to come after work where there's lots of space and it's close to the Metro.
Great restaurant
Had a portobello mushroom taco with quesadilla. It was ok. Service was good though.

The owner and staff of Mission are PHENOMENAL! We hosted a class event there and they took care of everything. It's a nice place, in a prime location, and they make a great margarita. Will be back again!
Really good guac, great sport for happy hour but watered down margaritas

This is a good Mexican restaurant in DuPont Circle. I liked my dish, but I made a modification while ordering that I ended up regretting. I hope to go back soon to try something different... the staff and the environment were great, so I feel like Mission has the potential to earn a 5-star rating from me.
Sort of a Midwex-mex place; not bad for by any means, but not the sorry of flavor you want from Mexican. Good margaritas, but definitely more of a happy hour place than a dinner place.
Just had a great impromptu dinner on the patio. Food was great and so was the service. I will be back!

I can't tell exactly what was so good about this place, but everyone in our group of 4 (myself included) was very satisfied with their meals and ate everything on our plates. Nice space too.

I ordered the tacos, I did not get the toppings concept as practiced as this place, there was no meat, just the stupid toppings, which were bad. Really awful. I was so unimpressed that I dare not order drinks. This place is the worst. The combination of rude, wait staff, serving barely digestible food, made this place the worst in DC.
